{"_id":"0v6KQ8U2d0Z8Kcmg","name":"Peregrine of the Cellar","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.0v6KQ8U2d0Z8Kcmg"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"a few hours","area":"a room","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Without fail, it detects the bacon, sausages and other food in a storeroom or cellar, and wine if desired. Its other use is the discovery of hidden chambers, which the wandering friar finds with a 1:2 probability if they contain anything edible. During fasting, it has another use, as it shows bacon, pork and so forth, and thus keeps the pious away from temptation. This makes it feasible the formula could have come from the Jews.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175533,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"2gJvtwIVWdTutVXb","name":"Transference","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.2gJvtwIVWdTutVXb"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"no more than a week","area":"one subject","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">With this method, the Cleric can lend a spell to a layperson, who may use it within a week. Until the spell is used, the week expires, or the subject dies, the Cleric cannot learn a new one to replace it.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175534,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"3UmQhknYX6GA919E","name":"Regretted Words","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.3UmQhknYX6GA919E"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"one week","area":"one person","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Sin is sin in the form of thought, word, action and omission; and this formula draws attention to its second kind, as someone who would speak ugliness, perfidy or evil with their mouth, will have centipedes, worms and cellar beetles come from between their lips. There is no acquittal until the week is over &ndash; but then there is no need to have a foul mouth either.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175534,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"6TMvRytuYLRMR0Rk","name":"Manifestation of Sin","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.6TMvRytuYLRMR0Rk"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"one minute","area":"one group","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It shows a radiant figure, on whom the onlookers shall see their personified sins and all the otherworldly punishment they can expect. This dismal spectacle is enough to make the cowardly sort of brigand run, or to make such miscreants uncertain about going through with their evil intentions. It is notable that this apparition is more terrible at night, for sins appear less macabre by daylight (+2 to saving throws). It is useless against those with high Virtue, for those who shun sin need not fear its consequences.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175535,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"EU2ZCYJVC411SmNE","name":"Righteousness of the Innocent","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.EU2ZCYJVC411SmNE"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"no more than a day","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The Cleric, or anyone he endows with this assistance, receives a Charisma of 18, but for only one purpose: to persuade others of the truth of an accused innocent.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">It only has effect if the defender has a high Virtue, and the accused at least 3, for the Lord turns his back on reprobates. If the accused is acquitted, they must go on pilgrimage within one month, or order a thanksgiving mass. But if the accused should indeed be guilty, the defender&rsquo;s Charisma shall fall to 3, and he will lose 2 points of Virtue for his misdeeds. This stems from the cloister of Saint Raymond the Unborn, but it is now spread to other parts.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175535,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"NuZW3VfmqZrdeKbQ","name":"Protection from Wild Animals","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.NuZW3VfmqZrdeKbQ"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"an hour","area":"wild animals","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Neither animals, nor wild beasts, dogs or horses trained to kill shall attack the Cleric. This mindfulness does not apply to their company, unless the Cleric prevents the ruckus by approaching the beasts and calming them with ten minutes of preaching. And those animals such as those under the control of witches, spellcasters and other devil&rsquo;s companions are eligible to a saving throw. If the company would harm them, or threaten their little ones, this shall break the miracle as if it never were. This is common in the monasteries of the Franciscan brothers.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175535,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"QeuXx6xNRWsXZ1A7","name":"Bell of Goodwill","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.QeuXx6xNRWsXZ1A7"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"-","duration":"one day","area":"one person","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p2\">This bell is only visible to the subject, next to whose head it floats, and it is the subject alone who hears its jingle when they would commit a sin. Hopefully, the warning will make them stay back from their deed &ndash; especially if they did not try to avoid the spell in the first place.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175535,"modifiedTime":1672331695126,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"VcxYhb29tf8PCEcI","name":"Bitter Nourishment","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.VcxYhb29tf8PCEcI"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"one day per level","area":"a table","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It renders food so bitter that even swallowing it should count as penance. Therefore, many take it for a punishment of Gluttony, although it has a noteworthy use: it gives +2 to saving throws against poison until the spell&rsquo;s time is over.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175536,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"ZoRLi75VjP7dRi9H","name":"Detect Undead","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.ZoRLi75VjP7dRi9H"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"1 hour per level","area":"around oneself","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It shows if there are undead lurking in the area, including their approximate total might; which can be meagre, sizeable, considerable, and finally very great. Whether this refers to several lesser undead or a single very significant one, the formula does not tell.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175536,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"bW62VGaer2gXyjPJ","name":"Commandment","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.bW62VGaer2gXyjPJ"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"5 minutes","area":"1 + 1 target/ 3 levels","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">Faith&rsquo;s might and authority is shown in the short commandment, which those who fail their saving throws will fulfil without hesitation. Thus, a sentry could open a door, a miser could open his purse, a group of brigands could grant passage, or a headsman could lay down his raised axe. If the command is against the nature and orders of the subjects, they may change their intentions after a short time has passed.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175536,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"ft7rMrus8lhOvJ3e","name":"Bless","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.ft7rMrus8lhOvJ3e"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"until end of predicament","area":"one group","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">There are many things which receive a customary blessing, e.g. holy matrimony, new stables, a wagon, a market, and others too numerous to list. It would not do to list every possible effect of this spell, but it shall be noted that one of its most common applications is to extend luck to the departing congregation &ndash; who will receive +1 to all checks in the next predicament they encounter. Another use is invoked in battle, where it also grants +2 to damage, but only until the affair&rsquo;s conclusion.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175537,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"gMcAHweNyjRpCgT9","name":"Comprehensive Sermon","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.gMcAHweNyjRpCgT9"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"< 3 hours","area":"hearers","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is not right if the flock does not listen to the Word. But should it start with this spell, they will become very attentive, and will not leave until it is all finished &ndash; in fact, even more people will come to hear the preacher. Those who would leave must roll a saving throw; and as long as the sermon is ongoing, neither the preacher nor their companions will be harmed. There are not many who would thus collect the birds</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">and wild beasts around them to preach the Good Book, but the Franciscan brothers have done all that and more miraculous things.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175537,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"iV1TP3rHI8TDJBoY","name":"Turnaround Spell","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.iV1TP3rHI8TDJBoY"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"one round per level","area":"a group's weapons","save":"deftness","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It is a particularly useful spell against those who would break the peace, for one word will turn their weapons &lsquo;gainst them. When they would roll to hit, they must also roll a Deftness save: if they fail, they will strike themselves.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175537,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"jQTwsJXTZORJ7qmy","name":"Detect Evil","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.jQTwsJXTZORJ7qmy"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"1 hour per level","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It shows nearby evil wills and objects, but only if they are genuinely rotten, Virtue 3 or below. Similarly, it can sense the might of this evil, which can be meagre, sizeable, considerable, and finally very great. Whether this refers to several smaller influences or a single very significant one, the formula does not tell.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175537,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"jxSQ7SGNzacdZjti","name":"There is No Greater Ass","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.jxSQ7SGNzacdZjti"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"one day, then until cockscrow","area":"one subject","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The sinful and thoughtless man often remains without a lesson. If he must learn proper behaviour, this spell comes in handy, for he can see the bad example on himself. Should he do anything so foolish or scatterbrained that an ass would not do so, he will grow the long ears of the same, and cry out: &ldquo;Hee haw! Hee haw! There is no greater ass!&rdquo; Every time he makes a foolish misstep, his ears will grow longer, and he can eat nothing but hay. Care must be taken, however, because if the ears are trimmed by the unwise, they will stay that way the other day.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175538,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"m1tsVIhjw8x4gkS4","name":"Judicious Lesson","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.m1tsVIhjw8x4gkS4"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"medium","duration":"until end of fight","area":"courtyard","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">The mischievous man must be taught a regular lesson, and &ndash; as the wise Solomon was wont to say in the Good Book &ndash; there is no better way than to be generous with the stick. Hence, this spell animates a stick, staff, or cudgel of this sort, in two different manners. In a fight, they may be sent against the enemy, fighting at level 1+1 by default; at 2+1 from third level, and at 3+1 from fifth level, with an AC of 12 and damage of 1d6+1 or 1d8+1. It causes no lasting damage, only dispensing a sound thrashing. With the other method, it can be used to guard a storeroom, chest, cellar or similar, and if a mischievous intruder would disturb it, the staff, propped against wall or bench, will rise and give them Hell. It can dispense one more strike than it has levels, but if the fool should flee from the scene of the crime, it will not follow, but settle down again. This lasts until the staff is broken.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175539,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"nYFi4X4G9C7z2foi","name":"True Visage","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.nYFi4X4G9C7z2foi"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"short","duration":"one minute","area":"one subject","save":"temptation","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">It removes all forms of masquerade or transformation from the target, and if they hide a particularly heavy sin, it shows its unmistakeable signs as well (e.g. a strangler would be seen with hands dripping blood, or a false witness with a lizard&rsquo;s tongue). It lasts for a minute even with a successful save, but a failed check will make it last for a full day. The real question is whom to use it on, and when.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175539,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"oBdB0PobfsQQinXv","name":"Bountiful Herbalist","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.oBdB0PobfsQQinXv"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"very long","duration":"one hour per level","area":"around oneself","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">If the Cleric needs some kind of herb, they must name what they want, and this spell will lead them to its place if it is found in range &ndash; although there is no guarantee the way will be either safe or easy. Only those who know what they seek can use the spell.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175539,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"sW6RFgJlFU3TG6Rw","name":"Discarded Burden","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.sW6RFgJlFU3TG6Rw"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"until removed","area":"one place","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">With this spell, the Cleric removes the holy cross from around their neck. Be it simple wood or gemstudded gold, it will suddenly become heavy like lead, and only seven strong men can move or lift its weight &ndash; but if an innocent with a Virtue of 21 would try, they will find it as light as a feather. The cross, if he or she is not the previous sort, even the Cleric may not again take up; a new one must be acquired, but until that time, they suffer a -2 against Temptation.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175539,"modifiedTime":1672331695127,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
{"_id":"wBQJGbZmSRSSQ83Z","name":"Soothing Balm","type":"spell","img":"icons/svg/daze.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.helveczia.cleric-spells-1.wBQJGbZmSRSSQ83Z"}},"system":{"level":"1","class":"cleric","range":"touch","duration":"instantaneous","area":"one person","save":"-","component":"","description":"<p class=\"p1\">This magic is for pain-ease, lesser wounds and small afflictions, for it heals 1d6 Hp and 1 more per two levels. It also dispels the effects of many harmful spells, but does not help with poison or disease.</p>"},"ownership":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"helveczia","systemVersion":"This is auto replaced","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672329175540,"modifiedTime":1672331695128,"lastModifiedBy":"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK"}}
